      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "(By United Press Leased Wirel\n\n\nSHELDON, Wash, Dec. 2.-The\nwomen of this town may be the\nfirst in Washington to enjoy the\nprivilege of the ballot. Following\nthe adoption of the equal suffrage\nlaw at the last state election, the\nwomen of this town asked for rul-\ning on when they can have the bal\nlot County Attorney T. P. Fisk Of\nMason county has ruled that the\nlaw is now operative and the wo-\nmen will vote at the city election\nnext Tuesday."
    }
